    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 1.18,
      "end": 6.8,
      "text": "This is a labor box recording. All labor box recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 7.68,
      "end": 12.24,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit laborbox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.6,
      "end": 17.12,
      "text": "Recorded by Patty McCoy in Hudson, Colorado.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 18.26,
      "end": 21.06,
      "text": "Aesos Fables, the wolf in the sheep.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 22.4,
      "end": 27.64,
      "text": "A wolf was worried and badly bitten by dogs and lay a long time for dead.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 27.64,
      "end": 34.26,
      "text": "By and by he began to revive and feeling very hungry, called out to a passing sheep,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 35.0,
      "end": 38.84,
      "text": "and said, would you kindly bring me some water from the stream close by?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 39.3,
      "end": 43.2,
      "text": "I can manage about beef if only I could get something to drink.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 44.1,
      "end": 48.08,
      "text": "But this sheep was no fool. I can quite understand, said he,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 48.64,
      "end": 53.18,
      "text": "that if I brought you the water, you would have no difficulty about the meat.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 53.18,
      "end": 57.5,
      "text": "Good morning and of the wolf in the sheep.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
